[MK] case called at 11:08am.
Defendant Dwaine Sanders in court with Attorney Karl E Huebner.  ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.  

ADA Hall indicates that the State is withdrawing its Motion to Amend the Criminal Complaint. The agreement of the parties today is that Mr. Sanders will enter a change-of-plea to the original Complaint. 

Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest" entered; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

The Court sentences Mr. Sanders to:
--serve sixty days in Jefferson County Jail, with Work-Release and Huber privileges, consecutive to any other sentence,  to commence on January 13, 2017 at 6:00pm 
--the Court authorizes transfer of the service of this jail term to another county conditional on it being served under the same conditions as would occur in the Jefferson County Jail; there is not to be any day-reporting or electronic monitoring or home determine or some other passive form of service of this jail term 
--0 days credit for time already served given
--pay costs of $443 [$243 plus $200 DNA surcharge] in $30 per month installments commencing on 2/2/17 and on the 2nd day of each month thereafter until paid in full; non-payment shall result in a 10 day jail term with Work-Release and Huber privileges.
The Court determines that Mr. Sanders has provided a DNA sample and the Court will not make a further order requiring the collection of DNA as part of its orders in this case 
recess 11:26am.
